iddlesex, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Burford, Shropshire, England":"Burford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cornwallis","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English: regional name for someone from Cornwall, a Normanized form of Middle English  <i>Cornwalish</i>.  Compare  Cornwall  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cornwall","meanings":["English:","habitational name from the county of Cornwall, which is named with the Old English tribal name <i>Cornwealas</i>. This is from <i>Kernow</i> (the term that the Cornish used to refer to themselves, a word of uncertain etymology, perhaps connected with a Celtic element meaning ‘horn, headland’), + Old English <i>wealas</i> ‘strangers, foreigners’, the term used by the Anglo-Saxons for British-speaking people.","variant of   Cornwell  ."]},{"name":"Cornish","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name for someone from the county of Cornwall, from Middle English <i>Cornish</i>, <i>Cornysh</i> formed on the analogy of <i>English</i>, which was usually Normanized as <i>Corneys</i>. Not surprisingly, the surname is common in adjacent Devon, but it is also established as far afield as Suffolk and London."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Cornwallis was born about 1300 as the son of Geoffrey Cornwall. He married Alice Teagle in 1330, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 26 August 1354, in Middlesex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1300–Aft 26 August 1354":"umbes 1300–pärast 26. augustit 1354","1300–1354":"1300–1354","1304–Female":"1304–Surnud","1333–1384":"1333–1384","1284–1335":"1284–1335","Aft 26 August 1354":"pärast 26. augustit 1354","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","1284":"1284","1304":"1304","1335":"1335","26 August 1354":"26. august 1354","1333":"1333","1 June 1335":"1. juuni 1335","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","about 1300":"umbes 1300","w.d. 26 Aug 1354":"26. august 1354","London, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"Middlesex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Burford, Shropshire, England":"Burford, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, England"},"fi":{"about 1300–Aft 26 August 1354":"noin 1300–26. elokuuta 1354 jälkeen","1300–1354":"1300–1354","1304–Female":"1304–Kuollut","1333–1384":"1333–1384","1284–1335":"1284–1335","Aft 26 August 1354":"26. elokuuta 1354 jälkeen","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","1284":"1284","1304":"1304","1335":"1335","26 August 1354":"26. elokuuta 1354","1333":"1333","1 June 1335":"1. kesäkuuta 1335","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","about 1300":"noin 1300","w.d. 26 Aug 1354":"26. elokuuta 1354","London, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"Middlesex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Burford, Shropshire, England":"Burford, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, England"},"fr":{"about 1300–Aft 26 August 1354":"environ 1300–après 26 août 1354","1300–1354":"1300–1354","1304–